com.camerontec.catalys.server.passwordstore

Class FilePasswordStoreWithMemoryBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.configuration.AbstractConfigurable
      • com.camerontec.catalys.server.component.ComponentHelper
        • com.camerontec.catalys.server.passwordstore.FilePasswordStoreWithMemoryBase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IComponent, IHasAttributes, IConfigurable, IRegisterable, IPasswordStore, IPasswordStoreWithMemory, IService
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ClearTextFilePasswordStore, EncryptedFilePasswordStore

    public abstract class FilePasswordStoreWithMemoryBase
extends ComponentHelper
implements IPasswordStoreWithMemory
    Simple persistent password store which obtains passwords from a clear text password file.

    The password file syntax is:

    • Lines beginning with whitespace or '#' are ignored
    • Each password entry is on a separate line
    • A single password entry has the following form:
      • username:password:YYYY-MM-DD

    The date specified in the password entry is the password activation date and is interpreted as the first day on which that password entry is valid. The current password entry for a given username is then the most recent entry with an activation date prior or equal to the current day.

    Any number of passwords may be configured into the future.

    This class is both a service and a component and therefore assumes a component specific lifecycle.

    This service also implements IPasswordStoreWithMemory using a plain text file. The format of the file is similar to the format of the password file except that it contains no activation date.

    Author:
    Itiviti
